Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4 servings). Halve @tomato{1}(halved lengthwise and thinly sliced into half-moons). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Mince @parsley{1/4%ounce}(minced).

Halve @falafel{10}(halved).

== Balsamic Onion & Tomato ==

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (@sugar{1%tsp} for 4 servings). Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in tomato, garlic, and half the parsley. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Refrigerate until ready to use in Step 6.

== Falafel ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add falafel and cook until golden and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

While falafel cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

== Creamy Parsley Sauce ==

In a second #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4.5%tbsp} and remaining parsley. Lightly season with salt and pepper.

Add water @?water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Assembly ==

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with falafel. Drizzle with half the parsley sauce. Top with balsamic onion and tomato (draining first) and sprinkle with @feta cheese{1/2%cup}. Drizzle with remaining parsley sauce and serve.